item.title: Trieste: Efficiently Exploring The Depths of Black-box Functions with TensorFlow

item.title: Assisting Human Decisions in Document Matching

item.title: Theory and Implementation of Complex-Valued Neural Networks
item.description: This work explains in detail the theory behind Complex-Valued Neural Network (CVNN), including Wirtinger calculus, complex backpropagation, and basic modules such as complex layers, complex activation functions, or complex weight initialization.

item.title: On marginal feature attributions of tree-based models
item.description: An important observation, showcased by experiments with XGBoost, LightGBM and CatBoost libraries, is that only a portion of all features appears in a tree from the ensemble; thus the complexity of computing marginal Shapley (or Owen or Banzhaf) feature attributions may be reduced.

item.title: Continuous Remote Sensing Image Super-Resolution based on Context Interaction in Implicit Function Space

item.title: Local Causal Discovery for Estimating Causal Effects
item.description: Even when the causal graph underlying our data is unknown, we can use observational data to narrow down the possible values that an average treatment effect (ATE) can take by (1) identifying the graph up to a Markov equivalence class; and (2) estimating that ATE for each graph in the class.
